	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Aarg&gt;There are many reasons why you should be a shaman. You get decent melee so you can act as a tank up to level 35. Your magic is both powerful DOTs and decent DDs. Shamans later on get AWESOME pets. They are also a solo-able class, meaning you can probably solo up to level 25. When you hit 35, you get a pet so you can solo again up to 50. When you hit 45, you can waste guards with no problem. You can kite at level 14, and you have some serious debuffers. You also have powerful magic resist drops. If your a troll, you get natural regeneration, and if that's stacked with rubi regen and chloroplast, your HPs will probably never stay down. Wizards get 1100HP DD spells, but we have a 1000 DOT, 600DOT disease, +300 HP buffs, 410 DDs, and pets that can hit for about 80 each. Shamans are also money makers because of sow and bind. If your an ogre, you get high STR, and if your a dark race shaman, you get infravision. Well, that's about all I can think of. Shamans are wayyyyyyy above awesome buffs. They can DOT like no other (maybe necro) DD decently, have a pet, and still can melee effectively up to level 50.<BR>
<BR>
I hope you choose the path of a shaman.
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
