	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			OK, little clarification. I'm Kail, lvl 50 shaman, Rodcet Nife server.<BR>
<BR>
I will tell you what you have to look forward to, since reading thru some posts on everlore I could actually feel my IQ lowering (tho actually not so much in the shaman section). OK the lowdown of a lvl 50 shaman, and ive grouped with lvl 50 of every class i believe, and know them well.<BR>
<BR>
DD - i've posted before, and people like to say otherwise, but our dds suck. At low mid level (24-29) they are mildly ok, and at 34 are ok again, max damage wise, but they are resisted much easier than others dds. at lvl 50, i almost never cast dd, since ours is worst. you say what? worst?<BR>
well. Mages are more, necros dd is actually more, CLERICS dd is more, all more more more. This mean we suck? hell no, I call lvl 49+ the complaint level, mostly because the people I group with complain about how out of balance shamans are, which i disagree but thats neither here no there. let me go over some benefits:<BR>
<BR>
Dots second to none, not even necros. go ahead as a 50 necro who has best dots. ask a lvl 20 necro he will prolly say necro, but ask a lvl 50 and they usually know. envenomed bolt does roughly 1300 damage, in approx 42 seconds. Scourge does roughly 2000 damage n 125 secs. both lvl 49 dots. until this point we are not the best, but 49+ shamans are superior on dots, bar none.<BR>
<BR>
Togor's Insects. ask a planes raiding party, Togors is our mob slow down debuff and absolutely phenomenal, (lvl 39) I melee stuff others dont even dream of with this spell it greatly lowers the attack speed.<BR>
<BR>
Pets. My lvl 49 pet, if maxed level is summoned can double hit for 51 and then bash/kick. i remind you necro pets maxed hit for 55. now im not even about to compare our pet to a necros pet, especially one dual wielding fs daggers, they are way too fast for us. but if you buff your pet he will have about the same hps little more. Yes necros can fear/darkness stuff to solo a lot. but a necro cannot, for example darkness/fear the frenzied ghoul, but i can solo with ease with  togor + pet + dots. (btw i love partnering with necros at this level, we can do so much as a team)<BR>
<BR>
Regen Regen Regen. for a long while I had an open challenge where i would duel any class in a straight melee duel, self buffs and just melee. Of course high lvl warriors, paladins and such ate this up thinkin an easy way to show them beating a lvl 50 in a duel. problem is i never lost, best opponent i beat was a 47 paladin, and that was with only a gatorsmash maul, not my scourge. heres the secret:regen. i truly wish i was a troll to have even more.<BR>
heres how. i had base regen of barb (1) add to this, chloroplast (+10) add to this my rubi bp (+5) and add to this the lvl 49 spell rage (+25) total regen:41 a tick. rage also adds 50 str and 50 ac, btw. so when i dueled that paladin, i had a 240 str (lvl 50 my str buff is +67) so. as a result, i was regenning 41 a tick, had alacrity on to combat the gatorsmash's painfully slow 70 delay and scored my record melee hit in that duel of 115. shamans can melee at lvl 50, dont let anyone tell you different.<BR>
<BR>
however does this mean you just melee everything and never die with that regen? no, rage makes you oom while its up, so i only cast it when the perverbial fecal matter has hit the fan.<BR>
<BR>
all in all, i would say shamans are at LEAST in top 2 soloers, if not the top at level 50, add to this our incredible usefullness in big raids, coupled with enchanters, and our known group strength of awesome buffs, we are a great class.<BR>
i wont say best, there are other classes that, when played by excellent players have boggled my mind but they can't solo, which depending on your style you may want to solo occasionally<BR>
<BR>
Anyhow this was long and drawn out far more than i intended. i dont check this page very often so i apologize if i dont respond right away to any questions. Peace, and hunt safe.<BR>
<BR>
--Kail<BR>

