			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Hi all.<BR>
<BR>
Retard&gt; My guesss is that a shaman will win because they can lay on their DOTs, regen themselves, heal themselves, and when their almost oom, they can cast Rage on themselves and melee the rest.<BR>
<BR>
Kakal&gt;You can tailor, but I wouldn't suggest it. I'm guessing your a troll or ogre, so you have extreamly low INT. That means your skill will barely gain. To tell you the truth, the only skill that is maxed out for my level is Meditation because I'm doing it so damn often. Alchemy is ok, but it is costly and doesn't have the player base that blacksmithy or tailoring would have. Anyway, if you wanted to be a tailor, you'd have to go to Neriak to buy the patterns, get cat or wolf or bear pelts to tailor, and if you fail (you probably will) you'll end up loosing money. I suggest making your money by either killing things or by looting guard corpses and selling leftover stuff from guard killers.
